headline: India's Vadilal Industries U.S. unit to make ice creams locally to cut imports
summary: (Reuters) -The U.S. subsidiary of India’s Vadilal Industries will start manufacturing ice cream at its local facility by the year-end to reduce dependence on imports and boost sales, an executive of the unit said on Friday.  Vadilal Industries USA currently imports a majority of its products from India.  U.S. President Donald Trump last month imposed tariffs of up to 50% on Indian goods, sending exporters of everything from apparel to frozen shrimp into a frenzy and forcing them to work out contingency plans.
